Sentencas: Pd-doped lanthanum strontium ferrite powders La0.6Sr0.4Fe1-xPdxO3-delta with x = 0.05, 0.1 (LSFPd05 and LSFPd10) are synthesized by combustion synthesis method and investigated as electrocatalysts for fuel and air electrodes of symmetric solid oxide fuel cells (SSOFCs).
Titulo: Pd-doped lanthanum ferrites for symmetric solid oxide fuel cells (SSOFCs)

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction (XRD), Rietveld refinement, surface area (BET), temperature programmed reaction (TPR) and temperature programmed oxidation (TPO) analyses are performed on LSFPd powders.
Titulo: Pd-doped lanthanum ferrites for symmetric solid oxide fuel cells (SSOFCs)

Sentencas: Electrical measurements both in oxidizing and reducing conditions are carried out on sintered pellets.
Titulo: Pd-doped lanthanum ferrites for symmetric solid oxide fuel cells (SSOFCs)

Sentencas: Electrolyte (La0.8Sr0.2 Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta) supported cells are prepared using LSFPd powders as electrodes.
Titulo: Pd-doped lanthanum ferrites for symmetric solid oxide fuel cells (SSOFCs)

Sentencas: The electrochemical performances are evaluated in hydrogen and methane mixtures and promising performance are revealed in terms of large power output density and low polarization resistance.
Titulo: Pd-doped lanthanum ferrites for symmetric solid oxide fuel cells (SSOFCs)
